B.QR=new A.zE(B.bs,"Users did not struggle with the complexity of the task itself \u2014 they struggled with not knowing where they were in the process. Every significant usability failure we observed mapped back to a missing or ambiguous progress signal.","Key insight",B.G3,B.CF,null)
B.R4=new A.dI("widgets/project/project_callout_block.dart","ProjectCalloutBlock","Use to elevate a single key insight, design principle, or warning that should not be missed. Works well between dense sections as a visual breath.",B.QR,null)
B.R0=new A.eu("Use a single-page form instead of a multi-step wizard","User testing showed that the wizard created a false sense of progress and increased drop-off at step 3.","Task completion improved by 18% in the follow-up test round.",B.ey)
B.QW=new A.eu("Defer the notification preferences screen to post-onboarding","Stakeholders wanted it up front. We argued it added friction before users had context to make meaningful choices.","Shipped with compromise: one opt-in toggle at step one, full settings deferred. Both sides partially satisfied.",B.nv)
B.QX=new A.eu("Introduced an inline confirmation pattern instead of a modal","Modals were blocking flow and causing accidental dismissal on mobile. Inline felt lower stakes.","Reduced perceived friction but required more implementation effort than estimated. Worth it for mobile, borderline on desktop.",B.jQ)
B.QT=new A.eu("Prioritised loading skeletons over a global spinner","Global spinners gave no spatial context. Skeletons reduced perceived wait time in earlier usability tests.","Users reported the interface felt faster. Engineering flagged complexity of per-component skeleton states.",B.ey)
